            {
              "text": "TileMap",
              "kind": "type"
            }
          ],
          "params": [],
          "returnType": "TileMap",
          "description": "Convert this parsed Tiled source model into a format-independent runtime TileMap from @codexo/exojs-tilemap. Only finite orthogonal maps with atlas tilesets are supported. A non-orthogonal or infinite map, or a collection-of-images tileset, throws TiledFormatError rather than silently producing wrong (misplaced) or empty geometry. Tile layers become renderable TileLayers, object groups become data-only ObjectLayers, and image layers become data-only ImageLayers; group layer children are flattened in document order. The returned TileMap does **not** own the tileset textures — they remain in the Loader cache. Destroying the returned map does not unload textures."
        },
